{
  "texts": [
    "The U-Net is proposed by Ronneberger et al. (2015).",
    "The architecture of U-Net is depicted in Fig. 7.",
    "U-Net is designed with a symmetrical ordering of encoder-decoder blocks to distinguish every pixel by extracting multi-scale feature maps using encoding the input and decoding it to output using the same resolution (Punn and Agarwal 2022).",
    "The U-Net is operated to segregate the overlapping regions using background pixels with an individual loss of each pixel.",
    "This process is defined through an energy function E as represented in Eq. 9."
  ]
}